# Cursor Rules for Ladybird

This directory contains Cursor Rules to help with Ladybird browser development.

## Rule Files

### Always Applied (Core Standards)
These rules are automatically applied to every request:

1. **[coding-style.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/coding-style.mdc)** - C++ coding style conventions
   - Naming conventions (snake_case, CamelCase, SCREAMING_CASE)
   - Member prefixes (m_, s_, g_)
   - Type conventions and casts
   - Comments and documentation

2. **[error-handling.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/error-handling.mdc)** - Error handling patterns
   - TRY(...) macro usage
   - MUST(...) macro usage  
   - Fallible constructors pattern
   - LibWeb error types (ErrorOr, ExceptionOr, SimpleException, DOMException)

3. **[smart-pointers.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/smart-pointers.mdc)** - Smart pointer patterns
   - OwnPtr/NonnullOwnPtr for single ownership
   - RefPtr/NonnullRefPtr for shared ownership
   - WeakPtr for observation
   - Construction helpers and manual adoption

4. **[contribution-guidelines.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/contribution-guidelines.mdc)** - Contribution standards
   - Commit message format (Category: Description)
   - Git workflow and review process
   - Code quality standards
   - Community guidelines

5. **[project-overview.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/project-overview.mdc)** - Project structure
   - Architecture overview
   - Core libraries and their purposes
   - Directory structure
   - Documentation index

### File-Type Specific (Applied by Pattern)

6. **[cpp-patterns.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/cpp-patterns.mdc)** - C++ patterns (`*.cpp`, `*.h`, `*.mm`)
   - ladybird_main() entry point
   - Collections (Array, Vector, FixedArray, Span)
   - String view literals
   - Source location debugging
   - Static assertions

7. **[libweb-patterns.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/libweb-patterns.mdc)** - LibWeb patterns (`Libraries/LibWeb/**/*`)
   - Spec implementation comments
   - IDL file conventions
   - Directory structure per spec
   - LibWeb-specific error handling

## Quick Reference

### Naming
```cpp
class MyClass;              // CamelCase for types
void my_function();         // snake_case for functions
int m_member_variable;      // m_ prefix for members
static int s_static_var;    // s_ prefix for statics
constexpr int MAX_SIZE = 10; // SCREAMING_CASE for constants
```

### Error Handling
```cpp
ErrorOr<T> function() {
    auto result = TRY(fallible_operation());
    MUST(cannot_fail_operation());
    return result;
}
```

### Smart Pointers
```cpp
auto owned = make<MyClass>();              // OwnPtr
auto shared = make_ref_counted<MyClass>(); // RefPtr
auto weak = shared->make_weak_ptr();       // WeakPtr
```

